Description: Fix CVE-2026-56370 out-of-bounds access in ConnectedComponentsImage
 ImageMagick before 7.1.2-19 (and 6.x before 6.9.13-44) contains an
 out-of-bounds access vulnerability in ConnectedComponentsImage() in
 magick/vision.c. When the connected-components:* artifact define
 specifies an invalid index, an out-of-bounds read/write of the
 object[] array can occur, potentially resulting in denial of service
 or code execution. This patch adds bounds checks (>= 0 and <
 component_image->colors) around the three object[] index assignments
 in the keep-top, keep-ids, and remove-ids handling paths.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick6/commit/60b4e60841b429d719c59144e2505c8b0135367d
