Description: CVE-2026-55597 - Fix subsampling_dx/subsampling_dy typo in WriteJP2Image
 Corrects a one-character logic error in coders/jp2.c where the Y-axis
 extent (jp2_image->y1) was computed using parameters->subsampling_dx
 instead of parameters->subsampling_dy. When encoding JP2 images with
 asymmetric chroma subsampling this produced an incorrect image height
 and led to an out-of-bounds heap write (CWE-787).
 .
 Backported from the ImageMagick6 upstream branch (commit d241c85d) with
 the surrounding context adjusted to match Debian 12's 6.9.11-60 tree
 (which lacks the (ssize_t) cast added in later 6.9.13 releases).
