Description: CVE-2026-55594 - Fix VectorGraphicsNestedTooDeeply in GetMVGMacros
 A missing depth check in the MVG (Magick Vector Graphics) decoder results
 in a stack overflow when a crafted image with deeply nested "push" tokens
 is processed. Add a MagickMaxRecursionDepth guard on nested "push" tokens
 in GetMVGMacros; on overflow raise DrawError "VectorGraphicsNestedTooDeeply".
 The static helper GetMVGMacros gains an ExceptionInfo* parameter so the
 error can be reported through the image's exception object; its single
 caller RenderMVGContent is updated accordingly.
 .
 The unrelated "end >= start" refactor from the upstream commit is
 intentionally omitted so that the bookworm 6.9.11-60 behaviour of the
 macro extraction path is preserved. Only the CVE-relevant changes are
 backported.
