Description: CVE-2026-55577 - harden MVG rendering against heap buffer overflow
 The MVG decoder can be tricked into an out-of-bounds write when a crafted
 image causes a Trace* helper or CheckPrimitiveExtent call to fail while the
 outer switch in RenderMVGContent continues to dereference primitive_info
 slots that were never fully initialised. This backport of upstream commit
 aa50186 hardens two areas:
 .
 1. CheckPrimitiveExtent now over-allocates by one PrimitiveInfo and
    initialises the trailing sentinel (primitive=UndefinedPrimitive,
    text=NULL) so that any downstream code that walks past the last live
    slot lands on a well-defined element instead of uninitialised heap.
 .
 2. RenderMVGContent gains explicit `if (status == MagickFalse) break;`
    guards after every Trace* call inside the primitive switch, so a
    failure in one helper cannot be masked by the following
    `i=(ssize_t) (j+primitive_info[j].coordinates);` update or by the next
    iteration of the outer while-loop.
 .
 This is a semantic port: the v6.9.11-60 tree in Debian 12 does not carry
 the `primitive_info=(*mvg_info.primitive_info);` refresh lines that appear
 in the upstream v6.9.13-51 fix (they belong to a later refactor that
 introduces stale-pointer refresh after every allocator call). The
 hardening added here is the minimal semantic equivalent for this branch.
Origin: backport, https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick6/commit/aa501868594acba70147a2175601b028abd49335
