Description: CVE-2026-55595 - fix infinite loop in connected-components keep-ids/remove-ids parser
 ImageMagick's ConnectedComponentsImage() parses the connected-components:keep-ids
 and connected-components:remove-ids artifacts using strtol(). When the artifact
 string contains characters that strtol() cannot convert (e.g. a stray non-digit
 that is neither a comma nor whitespace, or an empty argument), the end-pointer
 was set equal to the start pointer and the loop failed to advance, spinning
 forever and consuming CPU (denial of service, CWE-835).
 .
 The fix passes a separate end-pointer to strtol() and breaks out of the parsing
 loop when no digits were consumed (d == c), guaranteeing forward progress.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick6/commit/f102ddccceb30b38dd01f9d77025f51c9a5cc272
Author: Cristy <urban-warrior@imagemagick.org>
