Description: Fix CVE-2026-55628 — enforce PathPolicyDomain rights in ConcatenateImages
 The ConcatenateImages() helper used by the -concatenate option opens the
 caller-supplied argv paths with fopen_utf8() without consulting the
 configured security policy, allowing the operation to read from and
 write to filesystem paths that the policy would otherwise deny (policy
 bypass, CWE-73). See GHSA-82mp-vp5c-9pf7.
 .
 Upstream commit dcba7ee9 (ImageMagick 7.x) adds
 IsPathAuthorized(<rights>, path) checks before every fopen_utf8() in
 ConcatenateImages() and raises ThrowPolicyException() on denial. The
 7.x helpers do not exist on the 6.x branch shipped in Debian bookworm
 (6.9.11.60), so this backport uses the equivalent 6.x primitives:
   * IsPathAuthorized(rights, path)
       -> IsRightsAuthorized(PathPolicyDomain, rights, path)
   * ThrowPolicyException(path, MagickFalse)
       -> errno=EPERM; ThrowFileException(exception, PolicyError,
                         "NotAuthorized", path); return(MagickFalse);
     (ThrowFileException is a plain macro on 6.x — it does not return —
      so an explicit return(MagickFalse) is added to preserve the 7.x
      early-exit semantics.)
 .
 The 7.x hunks against MagickWand/magick-cli.c are omitted because the
 unified `magick` CLI does not exist on the 6.x branch. In 6.x,
 ConcatenateImages lives in wand/convert.c (the sole caller path via
 -concatenate).
