Description: Fix CVE-2026-53467 heap information disclosure in MNG decoder
 Two memcpy calls in ReadOneMNGImage (coders/png.c) used a raw element
 count instead of a byte count, so only length bytes were copied for
 pixel structures larger than one byte, leaving the tail of the
 destination buffer with prior heap contents. Change length ->
 length*sizeof(*next) so pixel-sized elements are fully copied and no
 uninitialized heap tail remains.
 .
